Source: libezv24
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Joerg Desch <github@jdesch.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9)
Standards-Version: 3.5.2

Package: libezv24-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: libezv24-1 (= ${source:Version})
Description: development files of the ezV24 library.
 This package hold all the files you need to develop
 applications which use libezV24 to access the serial
 ports.

Package: libezv24-1
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: runtime of the ezV24 library.
 The ezV24 library provides an easy to use programming interface to
 the serial ports of the *nix system. It uses the C posix API as
 base of it's work.
